#### Alfred State College to host 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships

Alfred State College will host the 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships on Feb. 19-22 at the Alfred State College Aquatic Center.

#### Alfred State College to host 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships

Alfred State College will host the 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships on Feb. 19-22 at the Alfred State College Aquatic Center.

The four-day event will feature the best swimmers and divers from the State University of New York Athletic Conference (SUNYAC). The SUNYAC is one of the premier NCAA Division III conferences in the country and includes Alfred State, Brockport, Buffalo State, Cortland, Fredonia, Geneseo, New Paltz, Oneonta, Oswego, and Potsdam.

The event will begin on Wednesday, Feb. 19, with the men’s and women’s 1-meter diving preliminaries at 1 p.m. and the finals at 6 p.m. The swimming events will begin on Thursday, Feb. 20, with preliminaries at 10 a.m. and finals at 6 p.m. The swimming events will continue on Friday, Feb. 21, and Saturday, Feb. 22, with preliminaries at 10 a.m. and finals at 6 p.m. each day. The men’s and women’s 3-meter diving preliminaries will be held on Friday, Feb. 21, at 1 p.m. with the finals at 6 p.m.

The Alfred State College Aquatic Center is a state-of-the-art facility that features a 50-meter by 25-yard pool with two moveable bulkheads, allowing the pool to be configured in a variety of ways. The facility also features a separate diving well with two 1-meter and two 3-meter diving boards. The facility has seating for 500 spectators.

The SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships will be webcast live at www.alfredstate.edu/streaming. Live results will also be available at www.alfredstate.edu/athletics.

For more information on the 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships, visit www.alfredstate.edu/athletics or www.sunyac.com.
